objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of atezolizumab in combination with bevacizumab compared with sorafenib on the basis of the co-primary efficacy endpoints of OS and IRF-assessed PFS according to RECIST v1.1.

endpoints.name: Overall Survival
endpoints.text: Overall survival is defined as the time from the date of randomization to the date of death from any cause.

endpoints.name: IRF-Assessed Progression-Free Survival
endpoints.text: Independent Review Facility-assessed PFS is defined as the time from randomization to the occurrence of disease progression as determined by the IRF according to RECIST v1.1, or death from any cause, whichever occurs first.

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoints
endpoints.text: Secondary Efficacy Endpoints (as listed in Section 6.4.2)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Efficacy Endpoints
endpoints.text: Exploratory Efficacy Endpoints (as listed in Section 6.4.3)

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand for Overall Survival
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with hepatocellular carcinoma meeting eligibility criteria (Global enrollment phase) Summary measure: Hazard ratio (stratified).

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of study treatment due to toxicity or other reasons

intercurrentEvents.name: Subsequent anti-cancer therapy
intercurrentEvents.text: Initiation of non-protocol anti-cancer therapies after progression

estimands.treatment: Atezolizumab 1200 mg IV + Bevacizumab 15 mg/kg IV every 21 days vs Sorafenib 400 mg BID
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with hepatocellular carcinoma meeting eligibility criteria (Global enrollment phase)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Time from randomization to death from any cause

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand for Progression-Free Survival
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with hepatocellular carcinoma meeting eligibility criteria (Global enrollment phase) Summary measure: Hazard ratio (stratified).

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of study treatment prior to progression

intercurrentEvents.name: Missing tumor assessments
intercurrentEvents.text: Patient has no post-baseline tumor assessments
